---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Breadcrumb from "../components/Breadcrumb.astro";
import CTAStrip from "../components/CTAStrip.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | doticrosst"
  description="Meet the team behind doticrosst. We build digital tools for hairdressers and barbers who want to grow without the tech headache."
>
  <div class="container">
    <Breadcrumb
      items={[
        { label: "Home", href: "/" },
        { label: "About" },
      ]}
    />
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-intro">
        <h1>Built by someone who gets it</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          doticrosst started with a simple observation: hairdressers and barbers
          are some of the most creative people around, but they're stuck paying
          through the nose for clunky software that doesn't work the way they do.
        </p>
        <p>
          We're a small digital agency with one mission -- strip out the
          overpriced SaaS tools, replace them with things that actually work, and
          give you back the time and money you're currently wasting on tech that
          should be simple.
        </p>
        <p>
          Whether it's a booking system that doesn't charge you per appointment,
          a website that actually shows up on Google, or automating the admin
          that eats into your day -- we handle it so you can focus on your
          clients.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Why doticrosst?</h2>
        <p>
          The name is a play on "dot the i's and cross the t's" -- attention to
          detail is what separates good work from great work. That applies to
          haircuts and it applies to digital.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-3">
        <div class="value-card">
          <h3>No bloat</h3>
          <p>
            We don't build things you don't need. Every feature earns its place
            by saving you time or making you money.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card">
          <h3>No lock-in</h3>
          <p>
            You own your website, your data, your systems. We build on open
            tools so you're never trapped by a vendor.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card">
          <h3>No jargon</h3>
          <p>
            We explain things in plain English. You'll always know what we're
            building, why, and what it costs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTAStrip
    heading="Let's have a chat"
    text="No pitch, no pressure. Just a conversation about where your business is and where you want it to go."
    buttonText="Book a Free Call"
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-intro {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .about-intro h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .about-intro p {
    color: var(--text-light);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    max-width: none;
  }

  .value-card {
    text-align: center;
    padding: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .value-card h3 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .value-card p {
    color: var(--text-light);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
</style>
